    "headline": "The Iran War Is Boosting This Farming Stock. Farmers Won’t Be Happy.",
    "summary": "The war in the Middle East has made it a bad time to be a farmer—and a good time to own one particular farming stock.  Shares of  CF Industries  which makes nitrogen and ammonia fertilizer, rose 1.2% to $117.14 on Monday.  Iran itself controls roughly 10% of the global market for urea, a key component in nitrogen fertilizer.",
